					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>Novellae on Maimonides' Mishneh Torah by Meir Kohen, a disciple of Meir of Rothenburg.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="1r" to="126v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Ḥidushim ῾al [Mishneh Torah] </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">חידושים על [משנה תורה]</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en">Kohen, Meʼir </persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he">כהן, מאיר </persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>There is an enumeration of the halakhot and mitsvot contained in the Mishneh Torah on folio 98v.</p>
								<p>Folios 1r-3r contain some additional notes on Mishneh Torah, in a cursive Italian hand of the 16th century.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<extent>126 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>205</height>
										<width>150</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>140</height>
										<width>100</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>126 folios (+ 1 unfoliated modern paper flyleaf at the beginning and 2 at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 8 leaves each, marked by catchwords and by signatures in Hebrew letters.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Lacunae after folios 19, 55.</p>
									<p>Folio 15 left blank by the scribe.</p>
									<p>Ink often rubbed off. Fading.</p>
									<p>Partly water-damaged.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="23" writtenLines="23">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Visible pricking and hard-point ruling.</p>
									<p>Scant marginal notes.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
